      • addNewZoo

        @PostMapping(value="/course",
             consumes="application/json")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<?> addNewZoo​(@Valid @RequestBody
                                                            @Valid Zoo newCourse)
                                                     throws java.net.URISyntaxException
        Given a complete Zoo Object, create a new Zoo record and accompanying telephone numbers and student course combinations
        Example: http://localhost:2019/zoos/course
        Parameters:
        newCourse - A complete new course to add including telephone numbers and student. Animals must already exist.
        Returns:
        A location header with the URI to the newly created course and a status of CREATED
        Throws:
        java.net.URISyntaxException - Exception if something does not work in creating the location header
        See Also:
        ZooService.save(Zoo)

      • putUpdateZoo

        @PutMapping(value="/course/{id}",
            consumes="application/json")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<?> putUpdateZoo​(@RequestBody
                                                               Zoo updateCourse,
                                                               @PathVariable
                                                               long id)
        Given a complete Zoo Object Given the course id, primary key, is in the course table, replace the Zoo record , course student combinations and telephone records.
        Example: http://localhost:2019/zoos/course/15
        Parameters:
        updateCourse - A complete Zoo including all instructors and animals to be used to replace the Zoo. Animal types must already exist.
        id - The primary key of the course you wish to replace.
        Returns:
        status of OK
        See Also:
        ZooService.save(Zoo)

      • patchUpdateUser

        @PatchMapping(value="/user/{id}",
              consumes="application/json")
public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<?> patchUpdateUser​(@RequestBody
                                                                  Zoo updateCourse,
                                                                  @PathVariable
                                                                  long id)
        Updates the course record associated with the given id with the provided data. Only the provided fields are affected. If an telephone number list or course student combination list is given, it replaces the list.
        Example: http://localhost:2019/zoos/course/7
        Parameters:
        updateCourse - An object containing values for just the fields that are being updated. All other fields are left NULL.
        id - The primary key of the user you wish to update.
        Returns:
        A status of OK
        See Also:
        ZooService.update(Zoo, long)
